The paper discusses a tool for property checking using incremental SAT, which is a common technique in the field of automated reasoning (cs.LO). The tool is designed to work with Verilog RTL examples, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of constrained functions, which could fall under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET). Finally, the paper discusses the use of AIGNET, which is a type of artificial intelligence, suggesting a possible connection to the field of robotics (cs.AR).
